SIMPLE: individualize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Individualize
<hw>In`di*vid"u*al*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Individualized</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Individualizing</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>individualiser</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To mark as an individual, or to distinguish from others by peculiar
properties; to invest with individuality; to give distinctive character
to; to make distinctive; to enable differentiation from others of
similar type; -- of properties of things.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>The peculiarities which <qex>individualize</qex> and distinguish
the humor of Addison.</q> <rj><qau>N. Drake.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>to render (a product or service) suitable to each
individual person by varying to some degree its characteristics; to
personalize.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> personalize, individualize, make personal, make more
personal.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To consider individually; to mention each
individual.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Individualizer</ent>⟦br⟧
